# ServerMon — Cursor Rules

## Validation

Run after every change:
- `pnpm lint` — zero errors and warnings
- `pnpm build` — must succeed

## Styling

- Use Tailwind semantic classes: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-card`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-primary`, `border-border`, `bg-secondary`, `text-destructive`, `bg-success`, `text-warning`
- NEVER hardcode colors (`bg-slate-900`, `text-indigo-400`, `#6366f1`)
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes

## Components

- Import from `@/components/ui/` — Button, Input, Card, Badge, Spinner, Skeleton
- Wrap widgets in `WidgetErrorBoundary`
- Use `useToast()` for user feedback
- Interactive elements need `min-h-[44px]` touch targets

## Patterns

- SSE: use `MetricsProvider` + `useMetrics()`, never create `new EventSource` in components
- Logging: use `createLogger('context')` from `@/lib/logger`, never bare console.log
- DB: `import connectDB from '@/lib/db'` (default export)
- API routes: always try/catch, return `{ error: "message" }`, add `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'` when accessing DB
- New pages: wrap in `<ProShell title="..." subtitle="...">`
- Mobile: use `dvh` not `vh`, `sm:hidden` / `hidden sm:block` for responsive tables

## Do Not

- Add `any` types — use `unknown` and narrow
- Add `eslint-disable` or `@ts-ignore`
- Add hardcoded colors — use theme tokens
- Add `console.log` in API routes — use the logger
- Commit `.env` files or secrets
